    "summary": "Retract: \"metaphysical\" + brief TN is sufficient",
    "content": "You are right — \"above-phenomenal\" is no longer needed inline. The author's own preceding paragraph already does the heavy lifting: it unpacks the 形/形而上 structure, critiques the directionality, and reinterprets 上. By the time the reader reaches the 道德仁义礼 sentence, they have the tools to see what 形而上 means.\n\nUse \"metaphysical\" in the running text (it is the conventional English term and the reader now knows what it conceals), with a brief TN that cross-references the earlier explanation: something like \"See the discussion above of 形而上 (metaphysical) as 'upon the phenomenal' rather than 'above the phenomenal.'\" That is enough to re-activate what the reader already learned.\n\nThe inline coinage was a solution to a problem the author already solved."
